<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Atriplex polycarpa </i>is an intricately branched shrub that grows to 2 m tall. The branches are gray to yellowish brown, with bark that sheds in long strips. The species is dioecious and reproduces by wind-dispersed seed that collects in a seed bank. Seedling establishment follows disturbance events associated with sufficient winter rain (Desert Workshop 2000, Garner and Munda 2003, Vasek and Barbour 1977). <br/>
<br/>
This facultative phreatophyte tolerates moderately saline conditions or xeric, nonsaline upland sites with shallow water tables. Its limited but varied salt tolerance and high drought tolerance interact to control water stress and define the broad habitat boundaries of the alliance. This is one of the most widespread saltbush alliances in the Mojave Desert (Sankary and Barbour 1972). </div>
</div>

    
	
	
