<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text">Flooding events, rather than fire, appear to be the natural disturbance agents for this alliance. However, upland settings, particularly in the San Joaquin Valley margins and surrounding foothills, may be subject to stand-replacing fire. Like most North American saltbush species, <i>Atriplex polycarpa </i>does not sprout if top-killed. Shrubs colonize after fire from off-site seed sources because this is a prolific seeder (Desert Workshop 2000).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
